MEM(3l)                   LDG Call                     MEM(3l)

NAME
    mem.ldg - A memory manager for Gem dynamical libraries.
              current version 0.50, May 2002.

DESCRIPTION
    The goal of this library is to supply to other LDG-libraries 
    some high-level memory functions. LDG-libraries cannot use 
    directly the C malloc() function because LDG needs usually to
    share the memory reserved by malloc() with its client. Use 
    directly the function ldg_Malloc() (ldg_Malloc() gets memory 
    directly from the system using the Malloc() and Mxalloc() 
    GEMDOS functions) is a bad idea if you need to allocate or
    desallocate a lot of time because the GEMDOS memory function 
    are bugged and contribute to fragment the memory.

    So, MEM.LDG offers the equivalent functions to malloc(),
    realloc(), free()... The memory obtained with these functions
    can be shared with others programs.

SYNOPSIS

   Each fonction admits an additionnal parameter (a context) which 
   identify client which use MEM.LDG. This parameter allows MEM.LDG 
   to allocate  separate bloc memory for each process. 
 
   Functions are prefixed with an underscore character '_'. 
   Functions without context parameter have no prefix and 
   are binded in mem.h using the AES application identificator
   as context. In general, we use these functions instead of
   context functions.

    void* _ldg_malloc( long size, long context);
    void* ldg_malloc( long size);

        prodives shared memory in a similar way than
        the malloc() function.

    void* _ldg_calloc( long size, long context);
    void* ldg_calloc( long size);

        similar to (*ldg_malloc)() excepted the memory is
        initialized to zero.

    void* _ldg_realloc( void *adr, long size, long context);
    void* ldg_realloc( void *adr, long size);
    
        dynamic reallocation of shared memory obtained
        with (*ldg_malloc)() (see realloc()).

    void _ldg_free( void *adr, long context);
    void ldg_free( void *adr);

        release the shared memory reserved with ldg_malloc()

    void _ldg_strdup( void *src, long context);
    void ldg_strdup( void *src);

        duplicate a string.

    void _ldg_allocmode( long mode, long context);
    void  ldg_allocmode( long mode);

        mode = 1 : set memory allocation to global mode
        mode = 0 : set memory allocation to private mode (default)

		This function should be call one time before any
		memory allocation request.

BINDING
    #include <ldg/mem.h>
    LDG *mem;
	int err, vers = 0x0050;

	err = ldg_mem_init( "mem.ldg", vers, &mem);

	/* err is a LDG code error (see ldg.hyp)
	 * vers is a number version required for mem.ldg 
	 */
	 
    /* compile and link your library with -lmem flag */
    
    /* At the end, you have to free up the library */
    ldg_close( mem, ldg_global);

BUGS
    Currently, any bugs are reported.

FUTUR

    With LDG.MEM, we have a global memory manager for all 
    LDG-library. It could be interesting to create some controls
    of this function, for example :
        - free memory used by crashed library,
        - set a maximum limit per library or for all library,
        - choice between TTram and STram ...

    Any ideas are welcome.

CREDITS
    This LDG uses the functions (modified) of MiNTLIB.

